4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
5 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 311.5 of Title 36, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. By March 31, 2028, and on a quarterly basis thereafter, each
9 insurer authorized to write personal and commercial property
10 insurance in this state shall file with the Oklahoma Insurance
11 Department a supplemental report with information regarding personal
12 and commercial residential property insurance policies in this
13 state. The report shall be filed electronically in the manner and
14 form prescribed by the Insurance Commissioner and in accordance with
15 any instructions on the Department's website. The supplemental
16 report shall include separate information for personal lines,
17 property policies, and commercial lines property policies. The
18 report shall, at a minimum, include the following information for
19 each ZIP code broken down by month:
20 1. Total number of policies in force at the end of each month;
21 2. Total number of policies canceled;
22 3. Total number of policies nonrenewed;
23 4. Number of new policies written;
24 5. Total written premium;
Req. No. 17179 Page 4

1 6. Is the insurer actively writing policies;
2 7. Number of policies that exclude wind coverage;
3 8. Number of new claims opened during each month;
4 9. Number of claims closed during each month;
5 10. Number of claims pending at the end of each month; and
6 11. Number of claims in which either the insurer or insured
7 invoked any form of alternative dispute resolution.
8 B. Supplemental quarterly reports filed with the Insurance
9 Commissioner pursuant to this section shall be treated as working
10 papers and documents as set out in subsection F of Section 309.4 of
11 this title.
12 C. The Insurance Commissioner may use supplemental quarterly
13 reports to assist in determining whether a market conduct
14 examination or investigation of an insurer should be conducted. For
15 purposes of completing a market conduct examination of any company
16 under Sections 309.1 through 309.7 of this title, the Insurance
17 Commissioner may, in the sole discretion of the Insurance
18 Commissioner, use supplemental quarterly reports or amendments or
19 addendums to such statements to assist in determining compliance
20 with the laws of this state and rules adopted by the Insurance
21 Commissioner and to support any regulatory actions initiated by the
22 Insurance Commissioner.
23 D. For any repeated violation of this section, the Insurance
24 Commissioner may, after notice and opportunity for a hearing,
Req. No. 17179 Page 5

1 subj ect an insurer to a civil penalty of up to One Thousand Dollars
2 ($1,000.00) for each occurrence, along with any other penalties set
3 forth in applicable law. The civil penalty may be enforced in the
4 same manner in which civil judgments may be enforced.
