1 7. Conviction of the named insured of a crime having as one of
2 its necessary elements an act increasing any hazard insured against.
3 B. D. An insurer shall give to the named insured at the mailing
4 address shown on a homeowner's policy, a written renewal notice that
5 shall include new premium, new deductible, new limits or coverage at
6 least thirty (30) days prior to the expiration date of the policy.
7 If the insurer fails to provide such notice, the premium,
8 deductible, limits and coverage provided to the named insurer prior
9 to the change shall remain in effect until notice is given or until
10 the effective date of replacement coverage obtained by the named
11 insured, whichever occurs first. If notice is given by mail, the
12 notice shall be deemed to have been given on the day the notice is
13 mailed. If the insured elects not to renew, any earned premium for
14 the period of extension of the terminated policy shall be calculated
15 pro rata at the lower of the current or previous year's rate. If
16 the insured accepts the renewal, the premium increase, if any, and
17 other changes shall be effective the day following the prior
18 policy's expiration or anniversary date.
19 C. E. In the event an insured cancels a homeowner's insurance
20 policy or any other personal residential insurance coverage, written
21 notice shall be provided by the insured to the insurer that provided
22 the coverage being canceled. The notice of cancellation shall
23 provide the date of the cancellation of the policy and the insurer
24
Req. No. 17179 Page 46

1 shal l reimburse the insured for any premiums paid for coverage
2 beyond the date of cancellation of the policy.
3 D. F. An insurer canceling a policy under subsection C E of
4 this section shall not be liable for claims arising after the date
5 of cancellation.
6 G. If an insurer denies a homeowner's claim, in whole or in
7 part, reduces coverage, refuses to issue, or refuses to renew a
8 homeowner's policy based solely on the use of video recordings or
9 photographs of the loss using aerial imaging, including drones,
10 driverless vehicle, or other machine that can move independently or
11 through remote control, the insurer shall establish, if not already
12 existing, a process allowing the homeowner to appeal such denial
13 within at least thirty (30) days of the homeowner's receipt of the
14 insurer's full and final determination on the claim or decision to
15 reduce coverage, refusal to issue, or refusal to renew the
16 homeowner's policy. The insurer's evaluation of an appeal pursuant
17 to this subsection shall include an in-person inspection of the
18 loss. A determination on the appeal shall be completed, and the
19 homeowner notified, within thirty (30) days of the request of the
20 appeal.
21 H. An insurer shall not refuse to issue or refuse to renew a
22 homeowner's policy insuring a residential structure with a roof that
23 is less than fifteen (15) years old solely because of the age of the
24 roof.
Req. No. 17179 Page 47

1 I. 1. For a roof that is at least fifteen (15) years old, an
2 insurer must allow a homeowner to have a roof inspection performed
3 by an authorized inspector at the homeowner's expense before
4 requiring the replacement of the roof of a residential structure as
5 a condition of issuing or renewing a homeowner's insurance policy.
6 The insurer may not refuse to issue or refuse to renew a homeowner's
7 insurance policy solely because of roof age if an inspection of the
8 roof of the residential structure performed by an authorized
9 inspector indicates that the roof has five (5) years or more of
10 useful life remaining.
11 2. As used in this section, the term "authorized inspector"
12 means an inspector who is approved by the insurer and who is:
13 a. a licensed adjuster as defined in Section 6202 of this
14 title,
15 b. a licensed home inspector as defined in Section 858-
16 622 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
17 c. a building code inspector certified under Section
18 1000.23 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
19 d. a registered roofing contractor pursuant to Section
20 1151.3 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
21 e. a professional engineer licensed under Section 475.12a
22 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes, or
23 f. a professional architect licensed under Section 46.8a
24 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
Req. No. 17179 Page 48

1 3. For purposes of this section, a roof's age shall be
2 calculated using the last date on which one hundred percent (100%)
3 of the roof's surface area was built or replaced in accordance with
4 the building code in effect at that time or the initial date of a
5 partial roof replacement with subsequent partial roof builds or
6 replacements that result in one hundred percent (100%) of the roof's
7 surface area being built or replaced.
8 J. For purposes of subsection A of this section, the following
9 definitions shall apply:
10 1. "Claim" means a contact with an insurer by an insured or
11 third party, as an assignee of the policy benefits, for the purpose
12 of seeking payment. A claim shall not include a report of loss by
13 the insured or any subsequent inquiries or inspection of loss if:
14 a. no payment if made,
15 b. the report of loss is withdrawn by the insured, or
16 c. coverage is denied by the insurer; and
17 2. "Inquiry" means a request for information regarding the
18 terms, conditions, or coverages offered under a property and
19 casualty insurance policy that does not result in a claim.
20 SECTION 18. This act shall become effective July 1, 2027.
